    {
      "title": "<span id=\"#30024\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">indignant</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(adj.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>源于拉丁语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">indignantem</span>（主格 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">indignans</span>），“不耐烦的，不情愿的，愤怒的”，是 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">indignari</span> “不满，生气，反感，认为不值得”的现在分词，源于 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">indignus</span> “不值得”，由 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">in-</span> “不，相反”（见 <a href=\"/cn/word/in-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of in- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">in-</a>（1））和 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">dignus</span> “价值（名词），值得，适当的，恰当的”组成，源于 PIE <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">*dek-no-</span>，是 <a href=\"/cn/word/*dek-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *dek- \" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">*dek-</a> “接受，接纳”的带后缀的形式。相关词： <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">Indignantly</span>。</p><ins class=\"adsbygoogle relative inline-block transition-all inline-block h-[250px] w-[300px]\" data-ad-slot=\"4000736339\" data-adtest=\"off\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins>"
    }
  ],
  "relate": [
    {
      "title": "indignance<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(n.)</div>",
      "html": "<p>1580年代，来自 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of indignant \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/indignant\">indignant</a> + <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of -ance \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/-ance\">-ance</a>，或者来自中世纪拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">indignantia</i>。 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">Indignancy</i> 于1778年被证实。</p>"
    },
    {
