etism \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/Docetism\">Docetism</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of docile \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/docile\">docile</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of docimacy \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/docimacy\">docimacy</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of doctor \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/doctor\">doctor</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of doctrine \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/doctrine\">doctrine</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of document \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/document\">document</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of dogma \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/dogma\">dogma</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of dogmatic \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/dogmatic\">dogmatic</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of doxology \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/doxology\">doxology</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of heterodox \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/heterodox\">heterodox</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of indignance \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/indignance\">indignance</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of indignant \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/indignant\">indignant</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of indignation \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/indignation\">indignation</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of indignity \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/indignity\">indignity</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of orthodox \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/orthodox\">orthodox</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of paradox \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/paradox\">paradox</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of synecdoche \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/synecdoche\">synecdoche</a>。</p><p>它是“荣誉，慷慨”的梵语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">daśasyati</i> 的假设来源，“献礼，赠予”的梵语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">dacati</i>，“出现，显得，认为”的希腊语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">dokein</i>，“接受”的希腊语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">dekhesthai</i>，”合适或适宜“的拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">decere</i>，“教导”的拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">docere</i>，“优美、装饰”的拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">decus</i> 的来源或证据。</p>"
